name: Celtics
summary: After a dominant regular season, the Boston Celtics aim to reach a "next level" in the playoffs. Despite speculation, the Celtics are not pursuing LeBron James' son in the upcoming draft. They recently extended Jrue Holiday's contract for $135 million, making it the largest second-apron contract in NBA history. In a bizarre incident, the Celtics made NBA history by becoming the first team to not attempt a single free throw in a game, leading to a record-low combined total of two free throw attempts with the Milwaukee Bucks. The Celtics are projecting potential landing spots for their top free agents, while Jrue Holiday expressed his reasons for choosing a long-term deal with the team. This historic incident has made headlines, with multiple sources reporting on the Celtics' unprecedented performance and its implications.

name: Masters cut line
summary: The Masters cut refers to the qualification threshold established at the end of the third round of the Masters Tournament, where players scoring above a designated cut score are eliminated from the tournament. The cut is typically set at the top 50 players plus ties. This year, Jordan Spieth, Justin Thomas, and Brian Harman were among the notable players who failed to make the cut at the Masters. Tiger Woods, on the other hand, made history by recording the 24th consecutive cut of his Masters career. The projected cut line undergoes adjustments throughout the tournament, influencing which players remain in contention for the title.

name: Lori and George Schappell
summary: The world's oldest conjoined twins, Lori and George Schappell, have passed away at the age of 62. The twins, who were connected at the head, defied medical expectations and lived a full and active life. They were born in Reading, Pennsylvania, in 1961 and spent their lives in the same town. Lori and George were known for their cheerful personalities and their love of music and movies. They were also active in their community and volunteered at a local hospital. The twins' passing has been met with sadness by their family, friends, and the community.

summary: Several news outlets are reporting that a Houston-based surgeon, Dr. Steve Bynon, has been accused of secretly denying liver transplants to eligible patients. Hospitals, including Memorial Hermann, have halted liver and kidney transplant programs following the discovery that Dr. Bynon manipulated patient records, affecting their eligibility status. The alleged actions of the surgeon have raised ethical concerns and led to hospital investigations. The situation has brought attention to the need for transparency and accountability in the organ transplant process to ensure equitable access and patient safety.
